  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries around the world. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key components typically include:\n\n1. Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n2. Reporting suspicious financial transactions\n3. Record-keeping mandates\n4. Customer due diligence\n5. Financial institution compliance checks\n\nMajor jurisdictions like the United States, European Union, United Kingdom, and many others have comprehensive AML laws and enforcement mechanisms.",
